notes: Match restarted after rain on 1 April 1996
ST Jayasuriya world record - fastest century in limited overs international in 48 balls, beating Mohammad Azharuddin's previous record of 62 balls.
ST Jayasuriya world record - most sixes in limited overs international - 11 sixes, beating Gordon Greenidge's previous record of 8.
Aamer Sohail world record - most runs conceded in a single over in limited overs international - 30 (Jayasuriya scored 29 and there was 1 wide)
World record - highest match aggregate in a limited overs international - total runs 664-19 in 99.4 overs

milestones.description: This is the highest match aggregate (664) involving teams Pakistan & Sri Lanka in ODIs
Jayasuriya has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (110) in an innings in ODIs for SL, going past de Silva's 86
Jayasuriya has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (11) in ODIs for SL, going past Jayasuriya's 6
Jayasuriya has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (11) in ODIs, going past Greenidge's 8
